(282, NULL, 'Blood Culture and sensitivity', 'EXP0282', '1400', '690', 'Within 7 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A blood culture and sensitivity test measures the presence of bacteria or fungi in the bloodstream and determines their susceptibility to antibiotics. This test involves taking a blood sample, which is then incubated to allow any microorganisms present to grow. If growth occurs, the specific type of bacteria or fungi is identified, and further testing is done to find out which antibiotics are most effective against them. This test is crucial for diagnosing bloodstream infections and guiding appropriate antibiotic treatment.', NULL, '<p>A blood culture and sensitivity test is a critical diagnostic procedure used to detect and identify bacteria or fungi present in the bloodstream and to determine their susceptibility to various antibiotics. The test begins with drawing a blood sample, which is then incubated in a special medium that promotes the growth of any microorganisms present. If microbial growth is detected, the specific type of bacteria or fungi is identified through various laboratory techniques. Following identification, sensitivity testing is conducted to ascertain which antibiotics are most effective in inhibiting the growth of the isolated microorganisms.</p><p>This test is essential for diagnosing serious infections such as septicemia, endocarditis, and other systemic infections. By identifying the causative agent and its antibiotic sensitivities, healthcare providers can tailor antibiotic therapy to effectively treat the infection, improving patient outcomes. The blood culture and sensitivity test is especially important in guiding treatment for patients with fever of unknown origin, immunocompromised individuals, and those showing signs of systemic infection.</p>', '<p>ब्लड कल्चर और सेंसिटिविटी टेस्ट एक महत्वपूर्ण डायग्नोस्टिक प्रक्रिया है जो खून में मौजूद बैक्टीरिया या फंगी को पहचानने और उनकी विभिन्न एंटीबायोटिक्स के प्रति संवेदनशीलता निर्धारित करने के लिए उपयोग की जाती है। इस टेस्ट की शुरुआत खून के नमूने को लेकर होती है, जिसे एक विशेष माध्यम में डाला जाता है जो माइक्रोऑर्गैनिज़्म की वृद्धि को प्रोत्साहित करता है। अगर माइक्रोबियल वृद्धि का पता चलता है, तो बैक्टीरिया या फंगी की विशिष्ट पहचान विभिन्न प्रयोगशाला तकनीकों के माध्यम से की जाती है। पहचान के बाद, सेंसिटिविटी टेस्ट किया जाता है ताकि यह निर्धारित किया जा सके कि कौन सी एंटीबायोटिक्स सबसे प्रभावी हैं।</p><p>यह टेस्ट गंभीर संक्रमणों जैसे सेप्सिस, एंडोकार्डाइटिस, और अन्य सिस्टम संक्रमणों के निदान के लिए आवश्यक है। इसका उपयोग कर के स्वास्थ्य देखभाल प्रदाता एंटीबायोटिक थेरपी को विशेष रूप से प्रभावी ढंग से तय कर सकते हैं, जिससे मरीज के परिणाम बेहतर होते हैं। यह टेस्ट विशेष रूप से उन मरीजों के उपचार में महत्वपूर्ण है जिनके पास अज्ञात बुखार होता है, इम्यूनोकॉम्प्रोमाइज्ड लोग होते हैं, या जो सिस्टम संक्रमण के संकेत दिखाते हैं।</p>', '2024-07-30 19:01:50', '2024-07-30 19:01:50', NULL, NULL),
(283, NULL, 'Thyphi Dot -IgM Rapid', 'EXP0283', '490', '295', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The **Typhi Dot IgM** test is used to detect the presence of immunoglobulin M (IgM) antibodies against *Salmonella typhi*, the bacterium responsible for typhoid fever. IgM antibodies typically appear early in the course of an infection, indicating a recent or acute infection with *Salmonella typhi*. This test is valuable for diagnosing typhoid fever, particularly in the context of symptoms such as prolonged fever, abdominal pain, and gastrointestinal issues. It helps distinguish typhoid fever from other febrile illnesses. The Typhi Dot IgM test is often used alongside other diagnostic methods to confirm the presence of the infection and guide appropriate treatment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-30 19:04:36', '2024-07-30 19:04:36', NULL, NULL),
(284, NULL, 'Stool Reducing Substance', 'EXP0284', '290', '140', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A stool reducing substance test measures the presence of undigested sugars (reducing substances) in the stool. It is used primarily to diagnose carbohydrate malabsorption, such as lactose intolerance or other disaccharidase deficiencies, in infants and children. The presence of reducing substances indicates that sugars are not being properly absorbed in the intestine and are being excreted in the stool. This test helps in identifying digestive disorders and guiding appropriate dietary modifications and treatments.', NULL, '<p>Stool reducing substance testing is a diagnostic procedure used to detect the presence of undigested sugars, such as lactose, glucose, fructose, and galactose, in a stool sample. This test is particularly useful for identifying carbohydrate malabsorption disorders. When these sugars are not properly absorbed in the intestine, they pass into the colon, where bacteria ferment them, leading to the production of acids and gases. The presence of reducing substances in the stool can indicate conditions such as lactose intolerance, disaccharidase deficiencies (e.g., sucrase-isomaltase deficiency), and other forms of carbohydrate malabsorption. This test is especially important in pediatric patients presenting with chronic diarrhea, bloating, and abdominal pain, helping to diagnose and manage gastrointestinal disorders. By identifying the specific malabsorption issue, healthcare providers can recommend appropriate dietary changes or treatments to improve digestive health and alleviate symptoms. Regular monitoring may be necessary to assess the effectiveness of dietary interventions and overall management.</p>', '<p>स्टूल रेड्यूसिंग सब्स्टेंस परीक्षण एक डायग्नोस्टिक प्रक्रिया है जो स्टूल सैंपल में पचाए बिना शर्करा, जैसे लैक्टोज, ग्लूकोज, फ्रुक्टोज, डायबिटीज और गैलेक्टोज की उपस्थिति का पता लगाने के लिए उपयोग की जाती है। यह परीक्षण विशेष रूप से कार्बोहाइड्रेट मालएब्जॉर्प्शन विकारों की पहचान के लिए उपयोगी है। जब ये शर्करा आंत में सही ढंग से अवशोषित नहीं होती हैं, तो वे कोलन में चली जाती हैं, जहां बैक्टीरिया उन्हें किण्वित कर एसिड और गैस का उत्पादन करते हैं। स्टूल में रेड्यूसिंग सब्स्टेंस की उपस्थिति से लैक्टोज इनटॉलेरेंस, डिसैकेराइडेस की कमी (जैसे, सुक्रेज-आइसोमाल्टेज की कमी) और कार्बोहाइड्रेट मालएब्जॉर्प्शन के अन्य रूप जैसी स्थितियों का संकेत मिल सकता है। यह परीक्षण विशेष रूप से उन बाल रोगियों के लिए महत्वपूर्ण है जिनमें क्रॉनिक डायरिया, ब्लोटिंग और पेट दर्द जैसे लक्षण होते हैं, जो गैस्ट्रोइंटेस्टाइनल विकारों का निदान और प्रबंधन करने में मदद करता है। विशिष्ट मालएब्जॉर्प्शन समस्या की पहचान करके, स्वास्थ्य प्रदाता उचित आहार परिवर्तन या उपचार की सिफारिश कर सकते हैं ताकि पाचन स्वास्थ्य में सुधार हो और लक्षणों से राहत मिले। आहार हस्तक्षेप की प्रभावशीलता और समग्र प्रबंधन का आकलन करने के लिए नियमित निगरानी आवश्यक हो सकती है।</p>', '2024-07-30 19:08:19', '2024-07-30 19:08:19', NULL, NULL),
(285, NULL, 'Calcium Ionized', 'EXP0285', '850', '390', 'Within 3 Days', 'Overnight fasting for 9-12 hours', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'An ionized calcium test measures the level of free calcium ions in the blood, which are not bound to proteins. This form of calcium is biologically active and crucial for various bodily functions, including muscle contraction, nerve function, and blood clotting. The test provides a more accurate reflection of calcium status than total calcium levels, especially in conditions affecting protein levels or pH balance. It\'s particularly useful in diagnosing and managing conditions like hypocalcemia, hypercalcemia, and parathyroid disorders.', NULL, '<p>Ionized calcium refers to the free, biologically active form of calcium in the blood, which is not bound to proteins like albumin. This form of calcium plays a critical role in many physiological processes, including muscle contraction, nerve transmission, blood clotting, and hormone secretion. Ionized calcium levels are tightly regulated by the parathyroid hormone, vitamin D, and the kidneys to maintain homeostasis.</p><p>Measuring ionized calcium provides a more accurate assessment of calcium status in the body compared to total calcium levels, especially in conditions that alter protein binding, such as kidney disease, liver disease, and changes in blood pH. This test is particularly important in critical care settings and for patients with suspected calcium metabolism disorders, as it helps diagnose and monitor conditions like hypocalcemia (low calcium levels) and hypercalcemia (high calcium levels). Accurate ionized calcium measurement is essential for guiding appropriate treatment and ensuring optimal physiological function.</p>', '<p>आयनित कैल्शियम रक्त में कैल्शियम का स्वतंत्र, जैविक रूप से सक्रिय रूप है, जो प्रोटीन जैसे एल्ब्यूमिन से बंधा नहीं होता है। कैल्शियम का यह रूप कई शारीरिक प्रक्रियाओं में महत्वपूर्ण भूमिका निभाता है, जिसमें मांसपेशियों का संकुचन, तंत्रिका संचरण, रक्त का थक्का बनना और हार्मोन स्राव शामिल हैं। आयनित कैल्शियम स्तरों को पैरेथायराइड हार्मोन, विटामिन डी और गुर्दे द्वारा होमियोस्टेसिस बनाए रखने के लिए सख्ती से नियंत्रित किया जाता है।</p><p>आयनित कैल्शियम को मापना शरीर में कैल्शियम की स्थिति का अधिक सटीक आकलन प्रदान करता है, विशेष रूप से उन स्थितियों में जो प्रोटीन बंधन को बदलती हैं, जैसे कि गुर्दे की बीमारी, यकृत रोग और रक्त पीएच में परिवर्तन। यह परीक्षण महत्वपूर्ण देखभाल सेटिंग्स में और संदिग्ध कैल्शियम चयापचय विकारों वाले रोगियों के लिए विशेष रूप से महत्वपूर्ण है, क्योंकि यह हाइपोकैल्सीमिया (कम कैल्शियम स्तर) और हाइपरकैल्सीमिया (उच्च कैल्शियम स्तर) जैसी स्थितियों का निदान और निगरानी करने में मदद करता है। सटीक आयनित कैल्शियम माप उपयुक्त उपचार मार्गदर्शन और इष्टतम शारीरिक कार्य सुनिश्चित करने के लिए आवश्यक है।</p>', '2024-07-30 19:11:56', '2024-07-30 19:11:56', NULL, NULL),
(286, NULL, 'ACR - Angiotensin Converting Enzyme', 'EXP0286', '1500', '790', 'Within 2 Days', 'Overnight Fasting for 9-12 hours', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'An ACE (Angiotensin-Converting Enzyme) test measures the level of ACE in the blood. ACE is an enzyme that plays a crucial role in regulating blood pressure by converting angiotensin I to angiotensin II, a potent vasoconstrictor. Elevated ACE levels can indicate sarcoidosis, an inflammatory disease that affects multiple organs, especially the lungs and lymph nodes. The ACE test helps in diagnosing and monitoring sarcoidosis and can also assist in evaluating other conditions affecting ACE production.', NULL, '<p>Angiotensin-Converting Enzyme (ACE) is an important enzyme in the renin-angiotensin system, which regulates blood pressure and fluid balance. ACE converts angiotensin I, an inactive peptide, into angiotensin II, a potent vasoconstrictor that increases blood pressure by constricting blood vessels. Angiotensin II also stimulates the release of aldosterone from the adrenal glands, promoting sodium and water retention by the kidneys, which further increases blood pressure.</p><p>Measuring ACE levels in the blood can be useful for diagnosing and monitoring certain medical conditions. Elevated ACE levels are commonly associated with sarcoidosis, a granulomatous disease that primarily affects the lungs and lymph nodes but can impact multiple organs. Monitoring ACE levels helps in assessing disease activity and the effectiveness of treatment in sarcoidosis patients. Additionally, ACE inhibitors, a class of medications that block the action of ACE, are widely used in the treatment of hypertension, heart failure, and certain kidney diseases, underscoring the enzyme\'s clinical significance.</p>', '<p>एंजियोटेंसिन-कनवर्टिंग एंजाइम (ACE) एक महत्वपूर्ण एंजाइम है जो रेनिन-एंजियोटेंसिन प्रणाली में रक्तचाप और तरल संतुलन को नियंत्रित करता है। ACE एंजियोटेंसिन I, एक निष्क्रिय पेप्टाइड, को एंजियोटेंसिन II में परिवर्तित करता है, जो एक शक्तिशाली वासोकन्स्ट्रिक्टर है और रक्त वाहिकाओं को संकुचित करके रक्तचाप को बढ़ाता है। एंजियोटेंसिन II एड्रेनल ग्रंथियों से एल्डोस्टेरोन की रिहाई को भी उत्तेजित करता है, जिससे गुर्दे द्वारा सोडियम और पानी का प्रतिधारण बढ़ जाता है, जो रक्तचाप को और बढ़ाता है।</p><p>रक्त में ACE स्तरों को मापना कुछ चिकित्सा स्थितियों का निदान और निगरानी करने के लिए उपयोगी हो सकता है। उच्च ACE स्तर आमतौर पर सारकॉइडोसिस के साथ जुड़े होते हैं, जो एक ग्रैनुलोमेटस बीमारी है जो मुख्य रूप से फेफड़ों और लसीका ग्रंथियों को प्रभावित करती है, लेकिन कई अंगों को प्रभावित कर सकती है। ACE स्तरों की निगरानी से रोग गतिविधि और सारकॉइडोसिस रोगियों में उपचार की प्रभावशीलता का मूल्यांकन करने में मदद मिलती है। इसके अतिरिक्त, ACE इन्हिबिटर, जो ACE की क्रिया को रोकते हैं, का उपयोग उच्च रक्तचाप, हृदय विफलता, और कुछ गुर्दे की बीमारियों के उपचार में व्यापक रूप से किया जाता है, जो एंजाइम की नैदानिक महत्व को रेखांकित करता है।</p>', '2024-07-30 19:15:12', '2024-07-30 19:15:12', NULL, NULL),
(287, NULL, 'Vitamin C', 'EXP0287', '7500', '3950', 'Within 7 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vitamin C, or ascorbic acid, is an essential nutrient crucial for the growth, development, and repair of body tissues. It supports immune function, collagen production, iron absorption, wound healing, and maintenance of cartilage, bones, and teeth. As an antioxidant, it helps protect cells from damage caused by free radicals. Humans cannot synthesize vitamin C, so it must be obtained from dietary sources like fruits and vegetables, particularly citrus fruits, strawberries, bell peppers, and leafy greens.', NULL, '<p>Vitamin C, also known as ascorbic acid, is a water-soluble vitamin essential for numerous bodily functions. It plays a crucial role in the synthesis of collagen, a protein vital for the maintenance of skin, blood vessels, bones, and cartilage. Additionally, vitamin C enhances the absorption of non-heme iron from plant-based foods, aiding in preventing iron deficiency anemia. It acts as a powerful antioxidant, neutralizing free radicals and thereby protecting cells from oxidative stress and damage.</p><p>Vitamin C is also significant for immune function, as it stimulates the production and function of white blood cells, which help defend the body against infections. Moreover, it aids in the repair and maintenance of tissues, wound healing, and the overall health of skin. Humans cannot synthesize vitamin C endogenously, making dietary intake essential. Rich sources of vitamin C include citrus fruits, berries, tomatoes, bell peppers, and leafy greens. Deficiency in vitamin C can lead to scurvy, characterized by symptoms such as fatigue, gum disease, and skin problems.</p>', '<p>विटामिन सी, जिसे एस्कॉर्बिक एसिड भी कहा जाता है, एक पानी में घुलनशील विटामिन है जो शरीर की अनेक महत्वपूर्ण कार्यों के लिए आवश्यक है। यह कोलाजेन के संश्लेषण में महत्वपूर्ण भूमिका निभाता है, जो त्वचा, रक्त वाहिकाओं, हड्डियों और उपास्थि के रखरखाव के लिए आवश्यक एक प्रोटीन है। इसके अतिरिक्त, विटामिन सी पौधों से प्राप्त होने वाले नॉन-हीम आयरन के अवशोषण को बढ़ाता है, जिससे आयरन की कमी से एनीमिया को रोकने में मदद मिलती है। यह एक शक्तिशाली एंटीऑक्सीडेंट के रूप में कार्य करता है, फ्री रेडिकल्स को निष्क्रिय करता है और इस प्रकार कोशिकाओं को ऑक्सीडेटिव तनाव और क्षति से बचाता है।</p><p>विटामिन सी प्रतिरक्षा प्रणाली के लिए भी महत्वपूर्ण है, क्योंकि यह श्वेत रक्त कोशिकाओं के उत्पादन और कार्य को उत्तेजित करता है, जो शरीर को संक्रमणों से बचाने में मदद करती हैं। इसके अलावा, यह ऊतकों की मरम्मत और रखरखाव, घाव भरने, और त्वचा के समग्र स्वास्थ्य में सहायता करता है। मनुष्य शरीर में स्वाभाविक रूप से विटामिन सी का संश्लेषण नहीं कर सकता है, इसलिए आहार के माध्यम से इसका सेवन आवश्यक है। विटामिन सी के समृद्ध स्रोतों में खट्टे फल, बेरीज़, टमाटर, बेल मिर्च और पत्तेदार साग शामिल हैं। विटामिन सी की कमी स्कर्वी का कारण बन सकती है, जिसके लक्षण थकान, मसूड़ों की बीमारी और त्वचा की समस्याएं हो सकते हैं।</p>', '2024-07-31 12:27:11', '2024-07-31 12:27:11', NULL, NULL),
(288, NULL, 'Aspergillus IgE', 'EXP0288', '2500', '1570', 'Within 2 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'An Aspergillus IgE test measures the levels of Immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibodies in the blood that are specific to Aspergillus, a common type of fungus. This test is used to identify allergic reactions to Aspergillus, which can lead to conditions such as allergic bronchopulmonary aspergillosis (ABPA) and other Aspergillus-related respiratory issues.\r\n\r\nElevated Aspergillus IgE levels indicate that the immune system has been sensitized to the fungus and is producing IgE antibodies in response. This sensitization can result in symptoms like coughing, wheezing, shortness of breath, and exacerbated asthma. The test helps in diagnosing and monitoring these allergic responses, guiding appropriate treatment plans for affected individuals.', NULL, '<p>Aspergillus IgE is a blood test that measures the levels of Immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibodies specific to Aspergillus, a common fungus found in the environment. This test is primarily used to diagnose and monitor allergic reactions to Aspergillus, such as allergic bronchopulmonary aspergillosis (ABPA) and severe asthma with fungal sensitization (SAFS).</p><p>When the immune system is exposed to Aspergillus, it can become sensitized and produce IgE antibodies as a defense mechanism. Elevated levels of Aspergillus-specific IgE indicate an allergic sensitization to this fungus. Symptoms of an Aspergillus allergy can include coughing, wheezing, shortness of breath, and exacerbation of asthma symptoms.</p><p>The Aspergillus IgE test is crucial for identifying the cause of these symptoms and guiding appropriate treatment. It helps healthcare providers tailor interventions such as antifungal medications, corticosteroids, or other therapies to manage the allergic response and improve patient outcomes. Regular monitoring of Aspergillus IgE levels can also aid in assessing the effectiveness of treatment strategies over time.</p>', '<p>Aspergillus IgE एक रक्त परीक्षण है जो Aspergillus, एक सामान्य कवक, के प्रति विशिष्ट इम्युनोग्लोबुलिन E (IgE) एंटीबॉडी के स्तर को मापता है। यह परीक्षण मुख्य रूप से Aspergillus के प्रति एलर्जिक प्रतिक्रियाओं, जैसे एलर्जिक ब्रोंकोपल्मोनरी एस्परगिलोसिस (ABPA) और कवक संवेदनशीलता के साथ गंभीर अस्थमा (SAFS) के निदान और निगरानी के लिए उपयोग किया जाता है।</p><p>जब प्रतिरक्षा प्रणाली Aspergillus के संपर्क में आती है, तो यह संवेदनशील हो सकती है और रक्षा तंत्र के रूप में IgE एंटीबॉडी का उत्पादन कर सकती है। Aspergillus-विशिष्ट IgE के ऊंचे स्तर इस कवक के प्रति एलर्जिक संवेदनशीलता को दर्शाते हैं। Aspergillus एलर्जी के लक्षणों में खांसी, घरघराहट, सांस की तकलीफ और अस्थमा के लक्षणों का बढ़ना शामिल हो सकता है।</p><p>Aspergillus IgE परीक्षण इन लक्षणों के कारण की पहचान करने और उचित उपचार मार्गदर्शन में महत्वपूर्ण है। यह स्वास्थ्य सेवा प्रदाताओं को एलर्जिक प्रतिक्रिया को प्रबंधित करने और रोगी के परिणामों में सुधार करने के लिए एंटीफंगल दवाओं, कोर्टिकोस्टेरॉयड, या अन्य उपचारों को अनुकूलित करने में मदद करता है। समय-समय पर Aspergillus IgE स्तर की निगरानी उपचार रणनीतियों की प्रभावशीलता का आकलन करने में भी सहायक हो सकती है।</p>', '2024-07-31 12:34:35', '2024-07-31 12:34:35', NULL, NULL),
(289, NULL, 'Procalcitonin', 'EXP0289', '2890', '1490', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Procalcitonin is a blood biomarker that measures the levels of procalcitonin, a precursor of the hormone calcitonin. Elevated levels indicate a bacterial infection or sepsis, as procalcitonin levels rise in response to bacterial toxins and systemic inflammation. This test helps differentiate between bacterial and viral infections, guiding appropriate antibiotic treatment. It is particularly useful in managing patients with suspected sepsis, lower respiratory tract infections, and other serious bacterial infections, aiding in early diagnosis and monitoring treatment effectiveness.', NULL, '<p>Procalcitonin is a peptide precursor of the hormone calcitonin, primarily produced by the thyroid gland. However, in response to bacterial infections, procalcitonin is also produced by various tissues and cells throughout the body. Its levels in the blood rise significantly during systemic bacterial infections and sepsis, making it a valuable biomarker for diagnosing and monitoring these conditions.</p><p>Procalcitonin levels remain low in viral infections and non-infectious inflammatory conditions, helping to distinguish bacterial infections from other causes of inflammation. This differentiation is crucial for guiding appropriate antibiotic therapy, reducing unnecessary antibiotic use, and combating antibiotic resistance.</p><p>The procalcitonin test is particularly useful in managing patients with suspected sepsis, lower respiratory tract infections, and other severe bacterial infections. By measuring procalcitonin levels, healthcare providers can make more informed decisions regarding the initiation, continuation, or cessation of antibiotic treatments, thereby improving patient outcomes and optimizing treatment strategies.</p>', NULL, '2024-07-31 12:47:35', '2024-07-31 12:47:35', NULL, NULL),
(290, NULL, 'Hepatitis B Envelope Antibody- Anti HBe Quantitative', 'EXP0290', '1500', '690', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not Mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A Hepatitis B envelope quantitative test measures the concentration of Hepatitis B e-antigen (HBeAg) in the blood. HBeAg is a protein produced by the Hepatitis B virus that indicates active viral replication and high infectivity. Elevated levels of HBeAg suggest a high level of viral activity, while low or undetectable levels may indicate reduced viral replication or response to treatment. This test helps evaluate the severity of Hepatitis B infection, monitor treatment effectiveness, and guide clinical decisions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 12:55:31', '2024-07-31 12:55:31', NULL, NULL),
(291, NULL, 'Hepatitis B surface Total Antibody - HBs-Ab Quantitative -Anti HBs', 'EXP0291', '1500', '690', 'Within 2 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A Hepatitis B surface total antibodies test measures the presence of antibodies against the Hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) in the blood. This test detects both the Hepatitis B surface antibody (anti-HBs) and the Hepatitis B core antibody (anti-HBc). A positive result generally indicates either past exposure to the virus or successful vaccination. It helps determine immunity status, assess recovery from a Hepatitis B infection, or confirm that the vaccination series was effective.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 13:06:00', '2024-07-31 13:06:00', NULL, NULL),
(292, NULL, 'HBsAg Quantitative by ELISA', 'EXP0292', '1800', '790', 'Next Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The HBsAg ELISA (Enzyme-Linked Immunosorbent Assay) test detects the presence of Hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) in the blood. HBsAg is a protein on the surface of the Hepatitis B virus, indicating active infection. This test is used to diagnose acute or chronic Hepatitis B infection. A positive result suggests that the person is currently infected with the virus, while a negative result indicates the absence of HBsAg, suggesting no current Hepatitis B infection.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 13:10:23', '2024-07-31 13:10:23', NULL, NULL),
(293, NULL, 'Serum Protein Electrophoresis', 'EXP0293', '1000', '580', 'Within 4 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Serum protein electrophoresis measures the levels and types of proteins in the blood by separating them based on their electrical charge and size. This test identifies and quantifies different protein fractions, including albumin and globulins (alpha-1, alpha-2, beta, and gamma globulins). It helps diagnose and monitor conditions such as multiple myeloma, liver disease, kidney disorders, and inflammatory or autoimmune diseases. Abnormal patterns can indicate specific health issues and guide further diagnostic evaluation.', NULL, '<p>Serum protein electrophoresis is a laboratory test that analyzes the proteins present in the blood serum by separating them based on their electrical charge and size using an electric field. This test measures the levels of various protein fractions, including albumin and globulins (alpha-1, alpha-2, beta, and gamma globulins). The separation process results in distinct bands on a gel or membrane, each representing different protein components.</p><p>This test is crucial for diagnosing and monitoring a range of conditions, such as multiple myeloma, chronic inflammatory diseases, liver disease, and kidney disorders. It can help identify abnormal protein levels or patterns, such as monoclonal gammopathy, which can be indicative of certain types of cancers or immune system disorders. By analyzing these patterns, healthcare providers can better understand underlying health issues, guide treatment plans, and monitor disease progression or response to therapy.</p>', '<p>सीरम प्रोटीन इलेक्ट्रोफोरेसिस एक प्रयोगशाला परीक्षण है जो रक्त के सीरम में उपस्थित प्रोटीनों का विश्लेषण करता है, इन्हें उनके विद्युत चार्ज और आकार के आधार पर अलग करता है। इस परीक्षण में विभिन्न प्रोटीन अंशों के स्तरों को मापा जाता है, जिसमें एल्ब्यूमिन और ग्लोबुलिन्स (अल्फा-1, अल्फा-2, बीटा, और गामा ग्लोबुलिन्स) शामिल हैं। पृथक्करण प्रक्रिया से एक जेल या झिल्ली पर विशिष्ट बैंड बनते हैं, जो विभिन्न प्रोटीन घटकों का प्रतिनिधित्व करते हैं।</p><p>यह परीक्षण विभिन्न स्थितियों, जैसे मल्टीपल मायलोमा, पुरानी सूजनात्मक बीमारियाँ, लिवर रोग, और किडनी विकारों का निदान और निगरानी करने के लिए महत्वपूर्ण है। यह असामान्य प्रोटीन स्तरों या पैटर्न की पहचान में मदद कर सकता है, जैसे मोनोक्लोनल गमोपैथी, जो कुछ प्रकार के कैंसर या प्रतिरक्षा प्रणाली विकारों का संकेत हो सकता है। इन पैटर्नों का विश्लेषण करके, स्वास्थ्य देखभाल प्रदाता स्वास्थ्य समस्याओं को बेहतर ढंग से समझ सकते हैं, उपचार योजनाओं को मार्गदर्शित कर सकते हैं, और रोग की प्रगति या उपचार की प्रतिक्रिया की निगरानी कर सकते हैं।</p>', '2024-07-31 13:17:19', '2024-07-31 13:17:19', NULL, NULL),
(294, NULL, 'Calcium-Urine Spot', 'EXP0294', '350', '190', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A calcium urine spot test measures the concentration of calcium in a single urine sample. It provides a snapshot of calcium levels at a specific moment, helping to assess calcium excretion and balance in the body. This test can identify abnormalities such as hypercalciuria (excess calcium) or hypocalciuria (low calcium) and is often used to investigate conditions related to bone metabolism, kidney stones, or parathyroid disorders, complementing other tests for comprehensive calcium evaluation.', NULL, '<p>A calcium urine spot test measures the concentration of calcium in a single urine sample, often used as an initial screening tool for evaluating calcium excretion and assessing calcium balance in the body. This test provides a snapshot of calcium levels in urine at a specific time, which can help identify abnormalities in calcium metabolism, such as hypercalciuria (excess calcium in urine) or hypocalciuria (low calcium in urine).</p><p>It is often used to investigate conditions related to bone metabolism, kidney stones, or parathyroid disorders. The results are typically interpreted alongside other tests, such as serum calcium levels and 24-hour urine calcium excretion, to provide a comprehensive view of calcium homeostasis. Elevated or decreased calcium levels in the urine can indicate issues such as kidney dysfunction, calcium absorption problems, or endocrine disorders, helping healthcare providers diagnose and manage conditions related to calcium metabolism and bone health.</p>', '<p>कैल्शियम यूरिन स्पॉट टेस्ट एक एकल मूत्र नमूने में कैल्शियम की सांद्रता को मापता है, जो अक्सर कैल्शियम उत्सर्जन का मूल्यांकन और शरीर में कैल्शियम संतुलन की जाँच के लिए प्रारंभिक स्क्रीनिंग उपकरण के रूप में उपयोग किया जाता है। यह परीक्षण मूत्र में कैल्शियम स्तर का एक तात्कालिक चित्र प्रदान करता है, जो कैल्शियम चयापचय में असामान्यताओं की पहचान करने में मदद कर सकता है, जैसे हाइपरकैल्सीयूरिया (मूत्र में अत्यधिक कैल्शियम) या हाइपो कॅल्सीयूरिया (मूत्र में कम कैल्शियम)।</p><p>यह परीक्षण आमतौर पर हड्डियों के मेटाबोलिज़्म, गुर्दे की पथरी, या पैरा थायरॉयड विकारों से संबंधित स्थितियों की जांच के लिए किया जाता है। परिणामों की सामान्यतः अन्य परीक्षणों, जैसे सीरम कैल्शियम स्तर और 24-घंटे के मूत्र कैल्शियम उत्सर्जन के साथ व्याख्या की जाती है, ताकि कैल्शियम होमियोस्टेसिस का समग्र दृश्य प्राप्त किया जा सके। मूत्र में कैल्शियम के स्तर में वृद्धि या कमी गुर्दे की कार्यक्षमता, कैल्शियम अवशोषण समस्याओं, या एंडोक्राइन विकारों जैसे मुद्दों को संकेत कर सकती है, जो स्वास्थ्य देखभाल प्रदाताओं को कैल्शियम चयापचय और हड्डियों के स्वास्थ्य से संबंधित स्थितियों का निदान और प्रबंधन करने में मदद करती है।</p>', '2024-07-31 13:25:29', '2024-07-31 13:25:29', NULL, NULL),
(295, NULL, 'ACTH - Adreno Cortico Tropic Hormone', 'EXP0295', '2800', '1290', 'Within 2 Days', 'Overnight fasting for 9-12 hours', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'An ACTH (adrenocorticotropic hormone) test measures the level of ACTH in the blood, which is produced by the pituitary gland. ACTH stimulates the adrenal glands to produce cortisol, a hormone that helps regulate metabolism, stress response, and inflammation. Elevated ACTH levels may indicate conditions such as Cushing\'s disease or Addison\'s disease, while low levels can suggest adrenal insufficiency or pituitary dysfunction. The test helps diagnose and monitor disorders related to adrenal gland and pituitary gland function.', NULL, '<p>ACTH (adrenocorticotropic hormone) is a hormone produced and secreted by the anterior pituitary gland. Its primary role is to stimulate the adrenal glands, specifically the adrenal cortex, to produce and release cortisol, a hormone essential for regulating metabolism, stress response, immune function, and inflammation. ACTH levels in the blood fluctuate throughout the day and are influenced by the body’s circadian rhythm.</p><p>The ACTH test is used to diagnose and monitor disorders related to adrenal and pituitary gland function. Elevated ACTH levels can indicate conditions such as Cushing\'s disease (where the pituitary gland produces too much ACTH), Addison\'s disease (adrenal insufficiency), or ectopic ACTH syndrome (where ACTH is produced by tumors outside the pituitary). Conversely, low ACTH levels can suggest secondary adrenal insufficiency or pituitary dysfunction. The test helps guide treatment decisions and evaluate the effectiveness of therapy for these disorders.</p>', '<p>ACTH (एड्रेनोकोर्टिकोट्रोपिक हार्मोन) एक हार्मोन है जो एंटेरियर पिट्यूटरी ग्रंथि द्वारा उत्पादित और स्रावित होता है। इसका मुख्य कार्य अधिवृक्क ग्रंथियों, विशेष रूप से अधिवृक्क कॉर्टेक्स को उत्तेजित करना है, ताकि यह कोर्टिसोल का उत्पादन और स्रावण कर सके। कोर्टिसोल एक हार्मोन है जो चयापचय, तनाव प्रतिक्रिया, प्रतिरक्षा प्रणाली, और सूजन को नियंत्रित करने में महत्वपूर्ण होता है। रक्त में ACTH स्तर दिनभर बदलते रहते हैं और शरीर की सर्कैडियन रिदम द्वारा प्रभावित होते हैं।</p><p>ACTH परीक्षण अधिवृक्क और पिट्यूटरी ग्रंथियों से संबंधित विकारों का निदान और निगरानी करने के लिए उपयोग किया जाता है। उच्च ACTH स्तर Cushing\'s रोग (जहां पिट्यूटरी ग्रंथि अत्यधिक ACTH उत्पन्न करती है), Addison\'s रोग (अधिवृक्क विफलता), या एक्टोपिक ACTH सिंड्रोम (जहां ACTH पिट्यूटरी के बाहर ट्यूमरों द्वारा उत्पादित होता है) का संकेत दे सकते हैं। इसके विपरीत, कम ACTH स्तर द्वितीयक अधिवृक्क विफलता या पिट्यूटरी विकार का सुझाव दे सकते हैं। यह परीक्षण उपचार निर्णयों को मार्गदर्शित करने और इन विकारों के लिए चिकित्सा की प्रभावशीलता का मूल्यांकन करने में मदद करता है।</p>', '2024-07-31 13:29:34', '2024-07-31 13:29:34', NULL, NULL),
(296, NULL, 'Allergy Aspergillus Fumigatus', 'EXP0296', '2800', '1680', 'Within 3 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'An allergy to Aspergillus fumigatus test measures the level of specific Immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibodies in the blood that react to the Aspergillus fumigatus fungus. Elevated IgE levels indicate an allergic sensitization to this fungus, which can cause respiratory issues such as allergic bronchopulmonary aspergillosis (ABPA) or exacerbate asthma. The test helps diagnose and manage allergic reactions to Aspergillus fumigatus by identifying sensitization and guiding appropriate treatment to reduce symptoms and improve respiratory health.', NULL, '<p>Allergy to Aspergillus fumigatus refers to an allergic reaction triggered by the Aspergillus fumigatus fungus, a common mold found in the environment. This type of allergy is characterized by the immune system\'s overreaction to the fungal spores, leading to the production of specific Immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibodies. Elevated IgE levels against Aspergillus fumigatus indicate sensitization to the fungus.</p><p>Symptoms of an Aspergillus fumigatus allergy can include coughing, wheezing, shortness of breath, and nasal congestion, often exacerbating conditions such as asthma. In more severe cases, it can lead to allergic bronchopulmonary aspergillosis (ABPA), a condition where the fungus causes inflammation and damage in the lungs.</p><p>Diagnosis involves measuring Aspergillus fumigatus-specific IgE levels through a blood test, which helps in confirming the allergy. Treatment typically includes allergen avoidance, corticosteroids, and other medications to manage symptoms and reduce inflammation, improving respiratory health and overall quality of life.</p>', NULL, '2024-07-31 13:34:25', '2024-07-31 13:34:25', NULL, NULL),
(297, NULL, 'dsDNA - Anti Double Standard DNA - IFA', 'EXP0297', '3000', '1675', 'Within 4 Days', 'Overnight fasting for 9-12 hours', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A dsDNA (double-stranded DNA) test measures the levels of antibodies against double-stranded DNA in the blood. Elevated levels of these antibodies are commonly associated with autoimmune diseases, particularly systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE). This test helps in diagnosing and monitoring SLE and assessing disease activity. High dsDNA antibody levels can indicate active disease or flares, while low levels may suggest disease remission or less activity. It is used alongside other tests to evaluate autoimmune conditions.', NULL, '<p>dsDNA (double-stranded DNA) is a test that measures the presence and concentration of antibodies against double-stranded DNA in the blood. These antibodies are produced by the immune system and are often associated with autoimmune diseases, particularly systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE). Elevated levels of anti-dsDNA antibodies are a key marker for SLE, and their measurement helps in diagnosing and assessing the activity of the disease. High levels of dsDNA antibodies can indicate disease flares or increased disease activity, while lower levels may suggest remission or reduced disease activity.</p><p>The dsDNA test is typically used in conjunction with other clinical assessments and laboratory tests to evaluate the severity and progression of SLE and to monitor the effectiveness of treatment. This test provides valuable information about the autoimmune response and helps guide therapeutic decisions to manage the condition effectively.</p>', NULL, '2024-07-31 13:38:34', '2024-07-31 13:38:34', NULL, NULL),
(298, NULL, 'Anti Thyroid Antibodies ( AMA+ ATG ) Panel', 'EXP0298', '2900', '1360', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '**AMA (Anti-Mitochondrial Antibodies)** and **ATG (Anti-Thyroid Globulin Antibodies)** are two different types of antibodies tested to diagnose autoimmune conditions:\r\n\r\n1. **AMA (Anti-Mitochondrial Antibodies):** These antibodies target mitochondria, the energy-producing structures within cells. High levels of AMA are primarily associated with primary biliary cholangitis (PBC), a chronic liver disease that damages the bile ducts. Testing for AMA helps in diagnosing and monitoring PBC.\r\n\r\n2. **ATG (Anti-Thyroid Globulin Antibodies):** These antibodies target thyroid globulin, a protein produced by the thyroid gland. Elevated levels of ATG can indicate autoimmune thyroid disorders such as Hashimoto\'s thyroiditis or Graves\' disease. Testing for ATG helps diagnose thyroid autoimmune conditions and guide treatment.\r\n\r\nBoth tests are important in identifying specific autoimmune diseases and assessing disease activity or progression.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 13:43:03', '2024-07-31 13:43:03', NULL, NULL),
(299, NULL, 'Aspergillus IgG', 'EXP0299', '2500', '1570', 'Within 2 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '**Aspergillus IgG antibodies** are a type of immunoglobulin G (IgG) antibodies produced by the immune system in response to an infection by Aspergillus, a common type of mold. The presence of Aspergillus IgG antibodies in the blood indicates a past or chronic infection with Aspergillus species.\r\n\r\n**Key points include:**\r\n\r\n- **Diagnostic Use:** Elevated Aspergillus IgG levels are used to diagnose chronic pulmonary aspergillosis (CPA), allergic bronchopulmonary aspergillosis (ABPA), and aspergilloma (fungus ball in the lungs).\r\n- **Chronic Infections:** Unlike Aspergillus IgE, which indicates an allergic reaction, IgG antibodies reflect a chronic or past infection.\r\n- **Clinical Relevance:** Measuring Aspergillus IgG helps healthcare providers determine the extent of the infection and monitor the effectiveness of treatment.\r\n\r\nThis test is particularly useful in patients with underlying lung conditions or compromised immune systems, where chronic Aspergillus infections are more common.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 13:45:44', '2024-07-31 13:45:44', NULL, NULL),
(300, NULL, 'Aspergillus IgM', 'EXP0300', '2500', '1570', 'Within 2 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '**Aspergillus IgM antibodies** are a type of immunoglobulin M (IgM) antibodies produced by the immune system in response to an infection by Aspergillus, a common mold found in the environment. The presence of Aspergillus IgM antibodies in the blood typically indicates an acute or recent infection with Aspergillus species.\r\n\r\n**Key points include:**\r\n\r\n- **Diagnostic Use:** Elevated Aspergillus IgM levels can help in diagnosing acute aspergillosis, an infection caused by Aspergillus fungi, particularly in immunocompromised individuals.\r\n- **Early Response:** IgM antibodies are usually the first antibodies produced by the immune system when it encounters a pathogen, indicating a recent or ongoing infection.\r\n- **Clinical Relevance:** Measuring Aspergillus IgM helps healthcare providers identify early stages of aspergillosis, allowing for timely intervention and treatment.\r\n\r\nThis test is particularly important for patients with weakened immune systems or those at high risk for fungal infections, as early detection and treatment are crucial for better outcomes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 13:47:01', '2024-07-31 13:47:01', NULL, NULL),
(301, NULL, 'Beta 2 Glycoprotein IgA', 'EXP0301', '1800', '980', 'Within 2 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '**Beta-2 glycoprotein I (beta-2 GP1) IgA antibodies** are a type of immunoglobulin A (IgA) antibodies directed against beta-2 glycoprotein I, a protein involved in the regulation of blood coagulation. These antibodies are associated with autoimmune conditions, particularly antiphospholipid syndrome (APS).\r\n\r\n**Key points include:**\r\n\r\n- **Diagnostic Use:** The presence of beta-2 GP1 IgA antibodies is used to help diagnose APS, a disorder characterized by blood clots, pregnancy complications, and other related issues.\r\n- **Clinical Relevance:** Measuring beta-2 GP1 IgA antibodies, along with other antiphospholipid antibodies (such as beta-2 GP1 IgG and IgM), helps in assessing the risk of thrombosis and guiding treatment decisions.\r\n- **Autoimmune Indicator:** Elevated levels of these antibodies indicate an autoimmune response where the immune system mistakenly targets beta-2 glycoprotein I, leading to increased blood clotting tendencies.\r\n\r\nTesting for beta-2 GP1 IgA is particularly important in patients who exhibit symptoms of APS or have unexplained blood clotting or pregnancy complications.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 13:51:25', '2024-07-31 13:51:25', NULL, NULL),
(302, NULL, 'Beta 2 Glycoprotein Panel- IgA IgG IgM', 'EXP0302', '5300', '2570', 'Within 2 Days', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '**Beta-2 glycoprotein I (beta-2 GP1) antibodies** are autoantibodies directed against beta-2 glycoprotein I, a protein involved in blood coagulation regulation. These antibodies can be of three types: IgA, IgG, and IgM. They are commonly associated with autoimmune conditions, particularly antiphospholipid syndrome (APS).\r\n\r\n**Key points include:**\r\n\r\n1. **Beta-2 GP1 IgA:**\r\n   - **Role:** Indicates an autoimmune response where the immune system mistakenly targets beta-2 glycoprotein I.\r\n   - **Clinical Use:** Helps diagnose APS, particularly in patients with unexplained blood clots or pregnancy complications.\r\n   \r\n2. **Beta-2 GP1 IgG:**\r\n   - **Role:** Strongly associated with APS and is one of the primary markers used in its diagnosis.\r\n   - **Clinical Use:** High levels suggest a high risk of thrombotic events and pregnancy complications.\r\n\r\n3. **Beta-2 GP1 IgM:**\r\n   - **Role:** Also involved in the immune response against beta-2 glycoprotein I.\r\n   - **Clinical Use:** Helps in the comprehensive assessment of APS and related conditions.\r\n\r\n**Diagnostic Use:**\r\n- **Antiphospholipid Syndrome (APS):** Presence of these antibodies is a key criterion for diagnosing APS, a disorder characterized by recurrent blood clots, pregnancy complications, and other issues related to abnormal blood coagulation.\r\n\r\n**Clinical Relevance:**\r\n- **Thrombosis Risk:** Elevated levels of these antibodies indicate an increased risk of developing blood clots.\r\n- **Treatment Guidance:** Measuring these antibodies helps in guiding treatment decisions, such as the use of anticoagulants, to manage and prevent complications associated with APS.\r\n\r\n**Overall Significance:**\r\nTesting for beta-2 GP1 antibodies (IgA, IgG, and IgM) provides valuable information for diagnosing and managing APS, aiding in the prevention of thrombotic events and improving patient outcomes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 13:59:36', '2024-07-31 13:59:36', NULL, NULL),
(303, NULL, 'Breast Monitor Panel * CA 15.3 * CEA', 'EXP0303', '3350', '1650', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '**CA 15-3** and **CEA (Carcinoembryonic Antigen)** are tumor markers used in the monitoring and management of certain types of cancers.\r\n\r\n### CA 15-3 (Cancer Antigen 15-3)\r\n\r\n**Definition:**\r\nCA 15-3 is a protein that is often elevated in the blood of individuals with breast cancer. It is a product of the MUC1 gene and is used primarily to monitor the treatment of breast cancer and detect recurrences.\r\n\r\n**Key Points:**\r\n- **Diagnostic Use:** CA 15-3 levels are measured to monitor the effectiveness of breast cancer treatment and to check for recurrence.\r\n- **Clinical Relevance:** High levels of CA 15-3 can indicate the presence of metastatic breast cancer. However, it can also be elevated in other conditions, such as ovarian cancer, lung cancer, and benign breast disease.\r\n\r\n### CEA (Carcinoembryonic Antigen)\r\n\r\n**Definition:**\r\nCEA is a glycoprotein involved in cell adhesion and is normally produced during fetal development. After birth, its levels drop significantly and are typically low in healthy adults. Elevated CEA levels can indicate certain types of cancer.\r\n\r\n**Key Points:**\r\n- **Diagnostic Use:** CEA is primarily used to monitor colorectal cancer, but it can also be elevated in other cancers, including breast, lung, pancreatic, and ovarian cancers.\r\n- **Clinical Relevance:** Elevated CEA levels are used to monitor cancer treatment effectiveness and to check for cancer recurrence. It can also be elevated in non-cancerous conditions such as inflammation, infection, and smoking.\r\n\r\n**Overall Significance:**\r\nBoth CA 15-3 and CEA are important tumor markers that help in the diagnosis, monitoring, and management of cancer. They provide valuable information about the presence and progression of cancer, aiding in the evaluation of treatment response and detection of recurrence. However, elevated levels of these markers should be interpreted with caution, as they can also be associated with non-cancerous conditions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 14:03:41', '2024-07-31 14:03:41', NULL, NULL),
(304, NULL, 'Urea Serum', 'EXP0304', '280', '140', 'Same Day', 'Fasting is not mandatory', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A urea test measures the amount of urea nitrogen in the blood. Urea is a waste product formed in the liver from the breakdown of proteins and is excreted by the kidneys. This test helps assess kidney function, as high levels of urea may indicate kidney dysfunction or failure, dehydration, or excessive protein intake. Conversely, low levels may suggest liver disease or malnutrition. The urea test is often part of a basic metabolic panel used to evaluate overall health.', NULL, '<p>Urea, also known as carbamide, is a waste product formed in the liver through the urea cycle from the breakdown of proteins. It is a colorless, crystalline substance that dissolves readily in water. Once produced, urea is transported via the bloodstream to the kidneys, where it is filtered out and excreted in urine. The primary function of urea is to remove excess nitrogen from the body, which is a byproduct of amino acid metabolism.</p><p>Clinically, the concentration of urea in the blood is measured as blood urea nitrogen (BUN) and serves as an important indicator of kidney function. Elevated BUN levels can indicate kidney dysfunction or failure, dehydration, a high protein diet, or gastrointestinal bleeding. Conversely, low BUN levels may suggest liver disease, malnutrition, or overhydration. Monitoring urea levels is crucial for diagnosing and managing various conditions related to the kidneys and liver, as well as assessing overall metabolic health.</p>', '<p>यूरिया, जिसे कार्बामाइड के नाम से भी जाना जाता है, यकृत में यूरिया चक्र के माध्यम से प्रोटीनों के टूटने से बनने वाला एक अपशिष्ट उत्पाद है। यह एक रंगहीन, क्रिस्टलीय पदार्थ है जो पानी में आसानी से घुल जाता है। एक बार बनने के बाद, यूरिया रक्त प्रवाह के माध्यम से गुर्दों तक पहुँचाया जाता है, जहाँ इसे छानकर मूत्र के रूप में उत्सर्जित किया जाता है। यूरिया का प्राथमिक कार्य शरीर से अतिरिक्त नाइट्रोजन को निकालना है, जो अमीनो एसिड चयापचय का उप-उत्पाद है।</p><p>चिकित्सकीय रूप से, रक्त में यूरिया की सांद्रता को रक्त यूरिया नाइट्रोजन (BUN) के रूप में मापा जाता है और यह गुर्दे की कार्यक्षमता का एक महत्वपूर्ण संकेतक है। उच्च BUN स्तर गुर्दे की खराबी या विफलता, निर्जलीकरण, उच्च प्रोटीन आहार, या जठरांत्र रक्तस्राव का संकेत दे सकते हैं। इसके विपरीत, निम्न BUN स्तर यकृत रोग, कुपोषण, या अधिक जलयोजन का संकेत दे सकते हैं। यूरिया के स्तर की निगरानी गुर्दे और यकृत से संबंधित विभिन्न स्थितियों का निदान और प्रबंधन करने के लिए और समग्र चयापचय स्वास्थ्य का मूल्यांकन करने के लिए महत्वपूर्ण है।</p>', '2024-07-31 14:15:06', '2024-07-31 14:15:06', NULL, NULL),
(305, NULL, 'Hepatitis B Viral ( HBV )DNA Quantitative -', 'EXP0305', '4700', '2900', 'Within 3 days', 'Overnight fasting for 9-12 hours', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '**HBV DNA quantitative test** measures the amount of hepatitis B virus (HBV) DNA in the blood. This test is used to evaluate the viral load in patients infected with HBV. \r\n\r\n**Key points include:**\r\n\r\n- **Diagnostic Use:** The test helps in diagnosing active HBV infection, monitoring the effectiveness of antiviral therapy, and assessing the risk of disease progression.\r\n- **Clinical Relevance:** A high viral load indicates active replication of the virus, suggesting a higher risk of liver damage, including chronic hepatitis, cirrhosis, and liver cancer.\r\n- **Treatment Monitoring:** By regularly measuring HBV DNA levels, healthcare providers can determine how well a patient is responding to treatment and make necessary adjustments to the therapeutic regimen.\r\n\r\nThe HBV DNA quantitative test is a crucial tool in the management of hepatitis B, aiding in early detection, treatment planning, and monitoring disease progression to improve patient outcomes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-07-31 14:18:15', '2024-07-31 14:18:15', NULL, NULL);
